ame":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Latherisk was born in 1142, in Aberdeenshire, Scotland as the son of William Latherisk Sr. He had at least 1 daughter. He died in 1225, in his hometown, at the age of 83."},"et":{"1142–1225":"1142–1225","1185–1250":"1185–1250","1120–1200":"1120–1200","1225":"1225","ABT 1200":"umbes 1200","1200":"1200","1142":"1142","1120":"1120","1185":"1185","1250":"1250","Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Aberdeenshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1142–1225":"1142–1225","1185–1250":"1185–1250","1120–1200":"1120–1200","1225":"1225","ABT 1200":"noin 1200","1200":"1200","1142":"1142","1120":"1120","1185":"1185","1250":"1250","Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Aberdeenshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1142–1225":"1142–1225","1185–1250":"1185–1250","1120–1200":"1120–1200","1225":"1225","ABT 1200":"environ 1200","1200":"1200","1142":"1142","1120":"1120","1185":"1185","1250":"1250","Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Aberdeenshire, Écosse","Scotland":"Écosse, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"William Latherisk est né en 1142, à Aberdeenshire, Écosse, fils de William Latherisk Sr. Il a eu au moins 1 fille. Il est décédé en 1225, dans sa ville natale, à l’âge de 83 ans."},"de":